From: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Date: Tue, 1 Oct 2013 19:04:40 -0700
Subject: net:drivers/net: Miscellaneous conversions to ETH_ALEN
Patch-mainline: v3.13-rc1
Git-commit: d458cdf712e0c671e8e819abb16ecd6e44f9daec (partial)
References: bug#909488 FATE#317387

Convert the memset/memcpy uses of 6 to ETH_ALEN
where appropriate.

Also convert some struct definitions and u8 array
declarations of [6] to ETH_ALEN.

Signed-off-by: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Acked-by: Arend van Spriel <arend@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Benjamin Poirier <bpoirier@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/vf.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/vf.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbevf/vf.c
@@ -242,7 +242,7 @@ static s32 ixgbevf_set_uc_addr_vf(struct
 	msgbuf[0] |= index << IXGBE_VT_MSGINFO_SHIFT;
 	msgbuf[0] |= IXGBE_VF_SET_MACVLAN;
 	if (addr)
-		memcpy(msg_addr, addr, 6);
+		memcpy(msg_addr, addr, ETH_ALEN);
 	ret_val = mbx->ops.write_posted(hw, msgbuf, 3);
 
 	if (!ret_val)
@@ -275,7 +275,7 @@ static s32 ixgbevf_set_rar_vf(struct ixg
 
 	memset(msgbuf, 0, sizeof(msgbuf));
 	msgbuf[0] = IXGBE_VF_SET_MAC_ADDR;
-	memcpy(msg_addr, addr, 6);
+	memcpy(msg_addr, addr, ETH_ALEN);
 	ret_val = mbx->ops.write_posted(hw, msgbuf, 3);
 
 	if (!ret_val)
